Starting from the different definitions of green initiatives proposed in the body of the literature (Iacob et al., 2013; Lieb and Lieb, 2010; Maas et al., 2012; Perotti et al., 2012; Pieters et al., 2012), Centobelli et al. (2017) proposed a novel definition of green initiative and developed a framework aimed to integrate the concepts of green practices, namely the set of specific organisational techniques and methods to achieve the sustainable goals, and enabling technologies, defined as the IT-based systems supporting green practices. This previous study proposed a taxonomy of LSP green practices (Table 1
                     ) and a taxonomy of LSP enabling technologies (Table 2
                     ).

For each type of green initiative t and for each phase of the service h, the GPS index (1, 2) represents the ratio between the average number of green practices adopted by the LSPs operating in each country k and the total number of green practices available (Table 10
                     ), whereas the ETS index (3,4) represents the ratio between the average number of enabling technologies adopted by the LSPs operating in each country and the total number of technologies available (Table 11
                     ).
